text:
wanted to reshare to honor dr. christine blasey ford for her nomination for the jfk profile in courage award. i wrote the poem below the day she gave testimony while crying in the bathroom at work with tears rolling down my face. i felt every single moment. dr. ford is a hero.

where were you when the world stood still?

i was watching the bravest woman on the planet speak her truth.

where were you when her voice cracked and shook?

i was at my desk with a hand to my chest and a lump in my throat. 
me too, i thought, as i took a deep breath for her.

where were you when these cowardly fools made her pain a spectacle? her anguish a sport? 
i was in the bathroom of my job with tears and deep breaths to keep my own pain hidden.

me too, i thought.

where were you when this man spewed his rage at his reckoning at everyone and everything, but himself?

i was tempering my rage at him and every man that deems truth a threat to their opportunity.

me too, i thought.

where were you when they tore her down and infantilized her hero status?

i was raising my fist and screaming in rejection, â€œi am with you. i believe you.â€ me too, we thought. âœŒ #metoo #drfordisahero #brave #courage
name: Kathryn Desai

text_retweet:
repost @backto_muslimidentity 
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€ kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, â€œtidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,â€ tukasnya.[] sumber:www.muslimahne

if youâ€™re worried a friend is being abused, let them know youâ€™ve noticed something is wrong.

they might not be ready to talk, but try to find quiet times when they can talk if they choose to.

if someone confides in you that theyâ€™re suffering domestic abuse: â€¢ listen, and take care not to blame them
â€¢ acknowledge it takes strength to talk to someone about experiencing abuse
â€¢ give them time to talk, but donâ€™t push them to talk if they donâ€™t want to
â€¢ acknowledge theyâ€™re in a frightening and difficult situation
â€¢ tell them nobody deserves to be threatened or beaten, despite what the abuser has said
â€¢ support them as a friend â€“ encourage them to express their feelings, and allow them to make their own decisions
â€¢ donâ€™t tell them to leave the relationship if theyâ€™re not ready â€“ thatâ€™s their decision
â€¢ ask if they have suffered physical harm â€“ if so, offer to go with them to a hospital or gp

text:
this pet project have been one on the most personal project i've worked on. ---------zahn othma perfume-----
i wanted to create a perfume brand that celebrate being the best that you can be while celebrating individuality and oneself.
--------------------------------------------------
when i was young, i was supposed to go to special needs school; i write letter bacwards, my writing doenst make sense and i was not like the other kids. in bording school, i lock myself in the shower,  washing my hands and face till its was sore, until i get the right "way" of washing it. 
i had alot of hurdle, people just dont get me. no matter how hard i try.
-------------------------------------------------
but luckily, there are those that took the time to know me better and took the time to understand where i was coming from. those relationships help me and it help me when everything seems to be agaist me. ------------------------
so, im dedicating and drawing inspiration from those relationships as inspirations for the brand. a perfume that is like a friend. it takes what what you are : the good, the odd and make it wonderful. ğŸ˜Š
-------------------
sorry its have taken me soo long to work on this project. the custome-blend perfume dept is open. so, call if you would like to get a custom blend scents. however, ready to wear collection is still in progress.  wish me the best guys! ---------------------- -#perfume #newperfume #scent #scents #ittars #smell #oud #ghost #perfumes #parfam #scented #weareintogether #metoo #together #relationship #positive #pma #positivementalattitude

text:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar adaÂ umbrella actÂ lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakanÂ #metooÂ yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™Â beijing platform for actionÂ (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagiÂ qawwamÂ (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepadaÂ mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.

.

text:
today was the day. .
.
the day when the excitement of launching â€˜beneath the veilâ€™ finally landed. i personally handed copies of btv to so many people today and i realised it is in the moment of the person receiving the book (and me hugging them) that i love the most about publishing a book. .
i completely adore the writing and editing process, but the in between there and here is a little transactional, where as this part is all heart. .
.
and now she is out there, i feel so free. there is no angst, no stress, no doubt - iâ€™m just surrendering and allowing her to do her thing, to find her way in the world, to find and connect to her readers and touch their souls. .
.
giving my sister her copy of btv this evening and knowing sheâ€™s probably already lying on the lounge reading, makes my heart sing. .

have you ever felt the joy of a dream in flight?

text:
10 years ago, i was fragile, i was scared, i was depressed, i had severe ptsd, i didn't want to leave my house, i hated myself, i was in a really bad place, i thought you broke me, i thought you had a hold over me because of what you took from me. 
10 years later i am the strongest i have ever been, i'm no longer afraid, i sleep a lot better, i can leave the house by myself.
it's taken me so long to over come what you did to me. 
but i did it. 
you are nothing. 
this tattoo is a reminder of how far i have come, how strong i am, how i am still whole. 
and thank you so much tanya smith for being there with me today getting one done with me! 
i wouldn't have made it this far without my parents, my family and my friends. whom i love dearly for all the support.
#survivor #newtattoos #sexualassaultawareness #inlove #fireroseunitysurvivortattoo #metoo @the.wolves.den

text:
â€¢dear daughter of mine,

i took your father to the kitchen and placed a pea in his hand; told him thatâ€™s how big his unborn child was at that moment â€“ that was how i broke the news of my pregnancy to him â€“ i had never seen a his face light up as it did that day.
when you were five months old, we heard your heartbeat for the first time and it was confirmed that you were a girl â€“ our daughter. just four months later, you were born, at 11:11am on 01/01/01.
as you grew up, our lives revolved around you. my favourite sound was that of your laughter as ricocheted off the walls of our living room. we loved you. 
we also worried for you.
you were born in a country where women were, both, revered and raped, worshipped and wounded, venerated and victimized; where pepper spray was a necessity and staying out after sunset was synonymous to suicide. you were born in an era when â€˜men of godâ€™ violated the sanctity of a womanâ€™s body and â€˜men in powerâ€™ didnâ€™t speak up. it was a country where the male population hid behind slogans of #notallmen â€“ what they didnâ€™t realize is that while #notallmen was in fact very much true, it was irrelevant because the greater truth was #yesallwomen and #metoo. cinderella might have been able to stay out with prince charming till midnight but it was safer for you to be back by 9pm. you grew up in a society â€˜big boys donâ€™t cryâ€™ and if they do, then they are asked to â€˜grow a pairâ€™ â€“ a society where misogynistic chauvinism was more prevalent than chivalry, a society where women were judged by the length of their denims and the width of their waist. there was a 0% tax on condoms but a 12% tax on sanitary pads â€“ both the commodities were considered inappropriate, though.
we protected you and we taught you how to protect yourself â€“ how to fight back. you were armed with an education, a positive outlook, a strong and loud voice that wouldnâ€™t hesitate to speak up and of course, pepper spray. i must say, youâ€™ve managed very well â€“ even better than myself! 
now, i worry for your children; and i wait for a day when the safety of our daughters is no longer something that worries us. 
awaiting the good times,
yours truly. â€¢

text:
#myfirstharassment

when i started this project, one year before the #metoo movement, i faced a lot of scepticism and denial about the ongoing harassment that women have been going through since their earliest years.  the 12 women who volunteered to tell me their first memory of harassment and offered me their portrait revealed the power of narrative in (re)building oneself and changing society.  their resilience impressed me, their courage gave me the strength to persevere.  today, as this project crosses the sea to london and #metoo has given women the opportunity to speak for themselves, i am even more convinced that when women speak, society moves forward. ã€°

the ministry of the interior's new investigation reveals that in 2018, complaints of rape increased by 17% in france.  women speak! ã€°

the two bis police officers accused of raping a canadian tourist in their office at 36 quai des orfÃ¨vres in 2014 were convicted of rape and sentenced to seven years in prison on thursday.  justice moves forward! ã€°ï¸ #personalispolitical #soundandvisualartist #womenvoices #feministart #socialart #socialchanges #committedart #artivist #lightbox #selfportrait #streetharassment #womenviolence #fightforyourrights #resilience #artist_sharing #clemencevazard #artwork #visualart

text: itâ€™s because of my experience that iâ€™ve talked about to the closest people that i was finally able to come to terms with not only physical but also mental insecurities. i struggle with anxiety, depression, weight,etc. and iâ€™m very open about showing it and talking about it because social media makes sure we only share the good parts of our life the â€œhighlightsâ€ but those who can show both are the true warriors and are the true representation and definition of strength- choosing to stay positive through the dark times! text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

entertainment | #metoo: iftda bans alok nath 
details:popular alok nath has been issued a six-month non-cooperative directive by the indian film and television directorsâ€™ association (iftda). the decision was taken as he had refused to show up for a posh (prevention of sexual harassment) inquiry. 
the actor was booked on november 22 for allegedly raping screenwriter and director vinta nanda, but later granted an anticipatory bail by the dindoshi sessions court.

last year, nanda had shared a detailed facebook post, wherein she had alleged that alok nath had sexually assaulted her. but the actor had denied the allegations.

#aloknath #bollywood #metoo #iftda #pratidintime

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

i wanted to take the opportunity to thank the people who helped me through the toughest experience of my life. 
link: https://bit.ly/2s3qmqh

to anyone who hasnâ€™t come forward, please use the incredible services available.

miss m said: â€œthe criminal process will continue to let people down until it changes.â€ fighting for justice, she said, had been harrowing at times, particularly as she continued to study and suffered from post traumatic stress disorder.

support from her family, friends, the university, police and fife rape and sexual assault centre were crucial.

she said: â€œst andrews university student services department went above and beyond to provide me with a world class service. â€œstudent services saw me at my very worst and it was because they believed in me that i was able to pick myself back up.â€ .

one of the best ted talks ever, that needs to be heard again and again in our society!  we will never achieve true gender equality without changing the way we raise boys first and then girls. i understand this may not be an issue in many countries, but the mascilist and patriarchal societies are still around us. i believe we are still on time to change that, we can still do something in our everyday life, even a small change in the way we treat each other, our family, our children and so on. we can achieve true happiness of men and women and i dream of one day that there will be no need for women even to speak up, and for people in general to speak up for equality. one day it will be so by default, and the change can start now!
.
.
.
.

text:
know the signs to help save the life of a child who is being sex trafficked!! one of the signs that can be a controversial discussion topic is attire. however, this isn't about passing judgment about what a young girl is wearing, it's about taking note of what she is (or isn't) wearing based on her age, environment, and who is accompanying her. for example, if you are in a hotel lobby and you a see young girl who looks to be about 12 years old and she has on a very revealing short dress, high heels and no jacket; it's 40 degrees outside, and she is with a man who appears to be 60, there is definitely cause for concern. keep in mind that it might be one sign that gets your attention initially and if you notice the child fits the profile for being a potential sex trafficking victim in other ways as well, listen to your gut instincts. if you are a victim or suspect that a child may be a victim of human trafficking, please call 911 or call the national human trafficking resource center at 1-888-373-7888 for help. all victims of slavery and human trafficking have rights and are protected by international, federal, and state law. 
the hotline is:â€¨(1) anonymous and confidential;â€¨(2) available 24 hours a day, seven days a week;â€¨(3) able to provide help, referral to services, training, and general information; (4) accessible in 170 languages;â€¨(5) operated by a nonprofit, nongovernmental organization; andâ€¨(6) toll free. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist  #superbowl @ga_cjcc

text:
r e s p o n s i b i l i yâ €
â €
i never really understood what it meant to be responsible. â €
â €
in school i got good grades, i wasn't a top student but i made sure my teachers were satisfied with my work.â €
â €
i helped out my parents when they asked with little complaints. i didn't want to get in trouble. â €
â €
i got a job when i was 16 and i did as my boss asked. i wanted to make her proud. â €
â €
adults always told both me and my parents how responsible i was for my age by comparing me to other kids in my class. â €
â €
but what happens when you grow up and move. who's watching you so you don't get in trouble, who are you trying to make proud, who are you comparing yourself to? was i really "responsible" or was i just pleasing others. â €
â €
looking back i know now. none of the success i had in my childhood was anything more than trying to satisfy someone else's version of me. â €
â €
you have to be responsible to yourself, and you have to be able to make yourself proud- especially when no one else is watching or there to hear about the successes. â €
let's pretend for a moment that all those people that you ever tried to make proud or please didn't exist. i know it's a grim thought, bare with me but really, what would you do with your life? what if just for a moment you asked yourself and you answered honestly to yourself because no one else needs to know...â €
â €
what makes you happy? â €
â €
and maybe you don't know the answer yet and that's okay. i encourage you to start your journey of self discovery and to seek out others that are on that journey too. â €
â €
for the last year, i've been apart of an amazing community, one that's let me really grow my wings. let's figured this thing called life out together, let's fly. â €

text:
a #metoo sensibility in workspace for women
#
modernwell is a shared workspace in minneapolis, minnesota. outside the building, the city is covered with snow and the temperature is well below freezing. but modernwell is warm and inviting. comfortable chairs and footrests surround the warmth of the fireplace. women work on laptops at tables around the room. there is not a man to be seen. that is because modernwell is one of a growing number of women-only and women-centered workspaces around the country. the increase of such spaces has been linked to the #metoo movement against sexual harassment and similar wrongdoing. the spaces represent a growing desire among many women to build a supportive environment at work that is different from the usual business culture. workplaces like modernwell provide more than just tables, chairs and a coffee maker. they also offer programs, like yoga and other fitness activities, a speakersâ€™ series and writing classes. in this january 16, 2019 photo, writer and editor camille lefevre, left, leads a pilates work at modernwell in minneapolis. renee powers is a modernwell member. â€œi think women, especially, are craving safe spaces...thereâ€™s no risk that somebodyâ€™s literally going to sexually harass me here,â€ powers said. she established her business, feminist book club,â€¦

#goodquote from a shirtless #boylover.

got a bunch of like #quotes but plato was to the point. he also championed "those who rise above the lies of their culture will never be believed nor understood by the masses." hashtag nambla is a banned hashtag. probably got too many "truther" tags on it. that's how #treasonrope and #darpabook became censored. all i did was use them, not start them.

i did start #usurpedgovernment and i'm still missing posts.

what other censored or banned hashtags have you discovered?

my studies of his social media platform show me ig protects #pederass folks. most people i showed the page said "that's disgusting." yet #darpabook2 aka ig said "this doesn't violate our policies." it was a minor in her knickers zoomed in on her bumbum. #smh.

the treachery is in our faces. and what do we do about it?

ignore it and hope the problem isn't that bad. #hope someone else fixes it. and hope it never happens to our kids. "hope. hmmmph. mankind's greatest downfall." the #architect, #thematrix.

the company exploiting minors on here, fyi, has miami in the name yet they're based in #canada with zero #usa presence other than social media.

but, nothing changes. we see the despicable acts and we just keep on keeping on.

it would be nice if the #metoo movement started advocating for children cuz the #hollywood #sexscene of coercing and #raping women is just the pinnacle of the iceberg. take the me too movement and multiply it. and those are just the things we know about.

here's a fact: i'd get charged and sentenced to 5 years in prison for selling cannabis in a dry state but if i were jeffrey epstein or a u.s. politician caught fucking a minor, i'd get less than 2 years and a largely suspended jail sentence.

#truth

in honor of #blackhistorymonth, we'll be highlighting black feminist leaders in our community, politics, the arts, and education across our facebook, twitter, and instagram channels.
âœ¨
today, we celebrate poet, playwright, novelist, and performance artist, ntozake shange. shange was just 27-years-old when her seminal play, â€œfor colored girls who have considered suicide/when the rainbow is enuf,â€ opened on broadway in 1976.
âœ¨
â€œfor colored girlsâ€ changed the world with its deeply beautiful, unprecedented depiction of lived trauma and black womanhood. the play won an obie award and received tony, grammy and emmy award nominations, and is today studied in classrooms across the country.
âœ¨
shange, who passed away in 2018 at the age of 70, was a prolific artist and champion for black women and girls. she will be remembered as one of the most important literary figures of our time.

text:
happy saturday birmingham! 
it is my honor to share this latest body of work for the #birminghamtimes with the city. #survivingsexualabuse #hiddenpain 
after viewing the #survivingrkelly docuseries, as a woman, i experienced a myriad of emotions. the empathy i felt resonated so deeply, that i wanted to become a vessel for our inner city survivors of sexual abuse. 
my gift is writing, and through my keystrokes i have the power to empower, cultivate change and advance a new and protective narrative that supports victims of sexual abuse. one that extends love, lends immediate empathy and a safe space for healing. 
through the courage and bravery each of these women, and by the sharing of their stories, they are lifting the veil on this mum subject. projecting truth into the community and revealing that these occurrences are often millions of familyâ€™s â€œbiggest secretsâ€, and hundreds of millions of women and girlsâ€™ unearned, undeserved greatest shame. #timesup for secrecy, #timesup for shame #timesup for #hiddenpain #metoo says #7evenrich #lashaundriabrown #aiechiahouse #angelwarren

this is only part 1, stay tuned next week for part 2, our final survivor stories and birmingham therapists weigh in. 
april â€˜7even richâ€™ richardson, your bravery has gone national. your story was picked up by #blackpressusa. even at 13-years young, you refused to stay silent. because of your courage, the community has been safe from your predator for a combined 20-years! ğŸ™ŒğŸ¾
thank you for empowering your city, and now the nation! ğŸ™ğŸ½ http://www.birminghamtimes.com/2019/01/surviving-sexual-abuse-april-7even-rich-richardson-taking-back-your-power/

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: many thoughts today. witnessed a beautiful american couple last night, inspired me to learn more of another language, it seems more important than my time put into languages that aren't as relavent. going to start drawing blended families and other humans as well, in time. that's another important part of what makes up this country. really loved playing smash up with my friends, everyone gets two decks of ghost, steampunk, aliens, plants ect. expansion decks and awesome, to strategize the blended allies, and host land. coexisting working together n such. in politics, i'm upset to report. growl. kamala harris, still better than the what is that thing in charge currently. although, as district attorney turned her back on over 600 open cases in her own state. food for thought objectively, not saying any commander in chief has ever been decent; they've all committed some form of genocide. not certain how 2020 is going to go, not saying she's in or out. i did like her before though. we've gotta be careful regardless. someone careful, and over themselves, rather than typical. also, as a country, being gracious hosts, and not when it only its met with favors would be decent. like ya know, the humans who shared kindly and helped william penn distribute land, before they were conned out of consenting to forceful misleading by his sons. recently watched annihilation a movie with natalie portman, good movie, still not ready to look at books on that topic so much, yet. learning about cells is weird. definetly willing too, yet, scared myself. the myth of gingers having no souls, is wrong, as in, religion has messed with their life expectancy too. gentle, gatherer ginger humans. mc1r gene, not carrier in every human, although matches well in the orient, they may be different in the eastern hemisphere, although still in existance. might have more info in time regardless, the earth is in more trouble than any bloodlines place upon it, coexisting is crucial. especially on levels like anyone we see daily, definetly discarding the bigots and predators, yet, there's too much to do at this time. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #polarvortex #blendedfamilies

#repost posted @withrepost from my instagram takeover with @shedoesthecity earlier this week. get your tickets to hook up! â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢

meet the creators of hook up- julie tepperman and chris thornborrow!! i remember when i first auditioned for julie and chris at the tapestry opera general auditons. when they invited me to the callbacks and told me what the piece was about, i knew that i really wanted to be a part of this show. the #metoo movement had just begun and was something that i wanted to engage in, but didnâ€™t know how. â€œhook upâ€ has allowed me the opportunity to examine these topics through theatre and share it with the community. 
iâ€™ve had conversations with both male and female friends regarding consent, and itâ€™s concerning to see how so many people seem to not understand or have different ideas of what consent means. 
only 1 in 3 canadians understand what sexual consent means.

in 82% of sexual assaults the perpetrator is known to the victim.

most perpetrators donâ€™t consider themselves perpetrators.

when i was growing up, sexual assault and consent werenâ€™t discussed a lot, either at home or in school. my hope is that this beautiful show that julie tepperman (librettist) and chris thornborrow (composer) created, which targets younger audiences, will be a way in which young people can engage in the conversation and bring awareness to these issues.

text: i was having a great conversation with a colleague today, which inspired me to post this. she felt that we are living in fear in our industry, held to silence under the threat of professional and financial repercussion. #metoo helped. but, these are long standing issues. the bulk of abusers are unnamed, still in power, still shielded from any repercussion. no remorse. so, iâ€™m making changes. iâ€™m refusing. iâ€™m preparing. and this is real power. iâ€™m changing what i can no longer accept. in this action and commitment, i thank the many incredible artists and professionals, mentors and students who do not engage in abuse, do not stand for it. our fight is young, iâ€™m grateful to find you fighting, grateful for your support and inspiration. #fightinjustice #humanrights #change #inspiration #artist #director #educator #dramaturg #choreographer #socialmediamarketing #picoftheday #angeladavis #thegoodfight #fightthegoodfight #consent #respect #support #community

text:
detail, panty line installation...
a frayed knot (or...afraid not)
the wash (as it seams) @msuunionartgallery .
spending time with the msu community following and in light of the nassar / title ix / msu abuse and neglect allows for the power of art to help individuals and the community heal.  power and peace to all of the sister survivors...may you find strength in your collective voices.
.

the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.
#exhibition #msu #uniongallery #contemporaryart #art #womeninthearts #feministart #feminism #installationart #installation #fiberart #gender #race #intersectionality #socialpractice #womenempowerment #women #womxn #metoo #sistersurvivors #thepersonalispolitical
name: Babette Shaw
tweet_full:
detail, panty line installation...
a frayed knot (or...afraid not)
the wash (as it seams) @msuunionartgallery .
spending time with the msu community following and in light of the nassar / title ix / msu abuse and neglect allows for the power of art to help individuals and the community heal.  power and peace to all of the sister survivors...may you find strength in your collective voices.
.

the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
next up in our performer line up is thea fitz-james! in her performance of "rich birch" thea fitz-james tells the true story of family kidnapping, feminist pirates, and delissio pizza. 'rich bitch' is a except from a larger work in progress piece about growing up poor and passing rich. 
thea fitz-james is part academic and part theatre practitioner. she holds a ba in theatre from mcgill, a bachelor of journalism from university of kingâ€™s college, and a masters in theatre & performance studies from york university. she is a phd candidate, working on a textiles in activism and performance, in theatre & performance studies at york university. she was a course director on theatre & social justice for york university theatre department in fall 2017, and organized a  panel on performing nasty feminism for catr, 2018. she is currently working on an article discussing #metoo in the canadian fringe festival community.

beyond her academic career, thea is an avid fringe performer and performance artist. she has curated performance festivals for the cucalorus festival, performed with fado and summerworks, and is one of the artistic directors for hub14. her solo performance piece, naked ladies, made international news when it was banned in singapore in 2017, and her artistic work has been discussed in tric and ctr. 
tickets to the feb 16th cabaret are on sale now. link to tickets in bio.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
meet our founder!!!
tyde-courtney edwards is the founding director of ballet after dark. she's also a classically trained ballerina, choreographer, art model and survivor of sexual assault. born and raised in baltimore city, she is a graduate of the baltimore school for the arts and has over 20 years of dance training and experience. trained in various styles of dance including classical and contemporary ballet, pointe, modern, lyrical, jazz, tap and hip-hop, she conceptualized ballet after dark after struggling with recovery following her sexual assault. tyde-courtney has trained with debbie allen dance academy, dance theatre of harlem, peabody conservatory, joffrey ballet, alvin ailey and other institutions while receiving training from local dance pioneers such as anton wilson, norma pera and stephanie powell. she currently resides in baltimore city.

we're healing at ballet after dark, llc... where every girl is a ballerina!ğŸ‘‘ be sure to visit the website today at www.balletafterdark.com! become a member and take advantage of new home workout and ballet tutorials being uploaded!

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the companyâ€™s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when youâ€™re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a personâ€™s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the â€œtraining setâ€ refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your â€œfeature setâ€: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, itâ€™s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data â€“ the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that youâ€™re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
part 1 out of 2 on the kesha-dr. luke case:
on october 14, 2014, kesha filed a lawsuit against dr. luke, her former producer, for allegedly forcing her to take date-rape drugs and then sexually abusing her. she also claimed (i say claimed because even though i believe her, nothing has been proved yet) that dr. luke employed emotional and psychological abuse on her, often calling her fat, which lead her to â€œsevere depression, post-traumatic stress, social isolation, and panic attacksâ€ (vulture). in this lawsuit, she asked to be released from her record deal with dr. luke. the same day luke filed a countersuit for defamation, saying that keshaâ€™s claims were all lies. fifteen days later he filed a lawsuit against pebe, keshaâ€™s mother. on june 10, 2015 kesha added sony to her original lawsuit, claiming sony knew about the abuse for years and put in â€œphysical dangerâ€ (vulture). in september kesha requests to be released from her record contracts with luke. she also requests that the court expedite her original lawsuit on dr. luke. sony also speaks out for the first time, claiming her suit is a â€œtransparent and misguided attempt to renegotiate her contractâ€ (vulture). on february 19, 2016 a judge denies keshaâ€™s request to be released from her contract with dr. luke because â€œthere has been no showing of irreparable harmâ€ (vulture). february 21 to march 7, fans and other celebrities voiced their support by boycotting sony and by donating money to help with keshaâ€™s legal bills. early april of 2016 kesha reveals that dr. luke would set her free from her record deal if she agreed to take back her rape allegations; kesha refused. on april 6, a judge throws out keshaâ€™s counter claims, stating that kesha was acting â€œunreasonablyâ€™ and that â€œevery rape is not a gender-motivated hate crimeâ€ (vulture). on may 22 kesha won her fight to perform at the billboard music awards after dr. luke tried to stop her from performing. dr. luke allowed her to sing if she did not mention him or the lawsuit. august 1, 2016: kesha drops her abuse lawsuit against dr. luke and puts all her efforts into being released from her contracts with dr. luke.

text:
(2/2)
famu students deserve a special mention in betty jean owens case, too. their immediate mass mobilization - after hearing that their classmate was assaulted - forced the grand jury to issue an indictment. patricia stephens due, mother of tananarive due and a fierce freedom fighter said that the case reverberated across campus, "we all felt violated, male and female," due said. "it was like all of us had been raped." look at the second picture on this post from the front page of the newspaper. it's a photo of one thousand students who gathered on the universityâ€™s quadrangle to demand justice for betty jean owens. the cover picture was taken on may 4, 1959 two days after the incident. two days isn't a whole lot of time to organize a successful protest with that many attendees, but the florida a&m students were very determined to get justice for their classmate. you can see the resolve in the students' faces. they were not going to allow those white men to get away with it. in fact, it was the famu students who would go on to lead the "jail no bail" tactic of the civil rights movement (made famous by the sit-ins and freedom riders). dr. martin luther king praised the students for "giving hope to all of us who struggle for human dignity and equal justice." and he argued that perhaps it was time to call on the human rights comm. of the un for help since u.s. justice was so often denied. the students stuck by owens side the whole time. in the first picture you see them outside the court house and in the last picture you see them inside the court house during owens trial. they filled every seat they could. thanks to betty jean owens courage to speak out and thanks to the pressure put on the grand jury by the students, justice for owens was served. âœ¨

february 2, 2019

"it was like all of us had been raped." look at the second picture on this post from the front page of the newspaper. it is a photo of one thousand students who gathered on the universityâ€™s quadrangle to demand justice for betty jean owens. the cover picture was taken on may 4, 1959 two days after the incident. two days is not a whole lot of time to organize a successful protest with that many attendees, but the florida a&m students were very determined to get justice for their classmate. you can see the resolve in the students' faces. they were not going to allow those white men to get away with it. in fact, it was the famu students who would go on to lead the "jail no bail" tactic of the civil rights movement (made famous by the sit-ins and freedom riders). dr. main luther king praised the students for "giving hope to all of us who struggle for human dignity and equal justice." and he argued that perhaps it was time to call on the human rights comm. of the un for help since u.s. justice was so often denied. the students stuck by owens side the whole time. in the first picture you see them outside the cou house and in the last picture you see them inside the cou house during owens trial. they filled every seat they could. thanks to betty jean owens courage to speak out and thanks to the pressure put on the grand jury by the students, justice for owens was served. âœ¨

text: i have spent the last three years learning how to begin to love myself. august 2016 i left a long term abusive relationship. an abusive relationship not just with a romantic partner, but an abusive relationship with myself. i have never treated myself with love, grace, or kindness. i've struggled with drug addiction, alcoholism, self-harm, eating disorders and various self destructive behaviors. while my healing is no where near completion, it is time i take this next step on my journey. i've focused on my emotional and spiritual well-being and now i must focus on my physical healing. join my sisters @tifiniesepiphanies @metamorphoollc and me as we continue to heal and grow together. one day at a time. one victory at a time. #healingjourney #weightlossjourney #domesticviolence #metamorphosis #sisterhood #metoo

text:
holy shit. so, i was reading this article to study something called, "indirect, unrelated punishment", right? from a psychological perspective, it helps me in my case against random house (my open push back against the race and gender exclusivity of the #metoo movement stimulated meg newmans cultural illiteracy and general state of medocrity, and she tried to punish me on the back end), so i'm reading various other like incidents as they apply to discrimination
.

newbold filed a discrimination claim against bc she has a rare form of dwarfism and he was "deliberately placing things outside her reach" (what a fuck off) and when she voted against kushners security clearance (very legal and within her base job description) he suspended her without pay
.

white people, man. just doing whatever they fucking want .

see, my book could fucking suck (and white people tend to think it does; they see no room for themselves in it. minorities love it), but it no longer matters. what does matter is meg newmans discrimination against me bc i'm technically disabled, and her punishment of me will make a full circle and bitch slap the fuck out her, as will klien's discrimination
.

and i think people shy away from their base disabilities bc it's "embarrassing", but i don't actually feel that way. i returned to work having recently been diagnosed with a brain tumor and she proceeded to treat me like shit, refusing any requests for help. that's fucking demented, not for me but for her
.

much like newbold, its seems reasonable to be awarded a position with the proper accommodations. i'm a straight a student, but if i ask for help it's necessary my colleagues provide it -- legally. it surpasses choice or preference
.

oh, the weird and fallen world of white "supremacy"
.

and i'm fine now bc the parameters of my disability aren't chronic, but acute and circumstantial, but when i sent her a note detailing my recovery, and said i would "perhaps need active editorial assistance" she just ignored it because she demands a disingenuous amount authority based primarily on humiliation. unwise
.

it's just not embarrassing to get sick. or be small. or just be not-white
.

_

give thanks to the kindness you received, and forgiveness to where is needed. this way, we keep our hearts clear of clutter and our love stronger than ever.

we will begin the week open to more opportunities, more love, kindness. knowing that the more love you give the more you will receive.

i wish everyone a blessed day

text:
hola. just your friendly abby here with a slight update. hasnâ€™t this just been the most exciting & fun two months ever? well, now itâ€™s february (thank god) and one day at a time iâ€™m finding my way back to myself again.

people have been overwhelmingly kind & generous throughout these trying times & i will never articulate a proper response to the love i feel from all of you. the other day, my dad came by to drop off panera on a particularly bad day. i did not except him & my step mom to have put together even more premium gel pens, a swear word coloring book, & #johannabrasford â€˜s 2019 coloring calendar.

iâ€™ve decided to do something this month. each month i want to plan to work on an area in my life that i feel i might be lacking in. this month, i chose self care. iâ€™ve written down a list of ultimate goals i want to achieve by the end of the month & small goals & daily steps to get there. then, each day will be colored & listed. i will have written in red the things i cannot not do; the things i have to accomplish. then in green i wrote down some fun options for the day, like outings i could join, walks i could go on, a joy ride, a treat yourself day, etc. then lastly in blue iâ€™ve listed a few daily goals on what to work on towards achieving my overarching ideal of self care. so far, itâ€™s been a really fun project & each day i will share that days photo & then also yesterdayâ€™s accomplishments to help myself. // we did find out that i have herniated 5 more discs in my lumbar spine after a tumble down some stairs & other violent injuries. so yes, iâ€™m in a wild amount of pain and will be needing a new walker for three weeks. iâ€™m not in good spirits, iâ€™m not happy, iâ€™m not hopeful. iâ€™m simply existing and trying to keep my head above water. maybe this will help. #spoonie #spooniestory #rape #metoo #tw #coloring #adultcoloring #selfcare #aboutme #dailygoals #chronicillness #gelpens #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #rapesurvivor #art

the distinctive "chicago style" of jazz originated in southern musicians moving north after 1917, bringing with them the new orleans "dixieland" or sometimes called "hot jazz" styles.

king oliver and jelly roll morton became stars of the chicago jazz scene. louis armstrong's recordings with his chicago-based louis armstrong and his hot five and hot seven band came out in the years 1925 to 1928. these recordings marked the transition of original new orleans jazz to a more sophisticated type of american improvised music with more emphasis on solo choruses instead of just little solo breaks. 
andyâ€™s jazz club is one of chicago's best-known and most-respected jazz establishments, historic andy's offers casually sophisticated dining with a musical menu of chicago's top jazz artists.

greg rockingham - drums
lee rothenberg - guitar
ken gueno - congas and percussion
(special guest)  greg ward - saxophone

chris foreman is a masterful musician and heir to the throne occupied by the soulful, bluesy jazz organ legends who were once his influence. blind at birth, foreman started playing piano at age five and began formal training at seven.

text:
almost five years ago my husband and i hit the epirb on our boat and initiated an at-sea rescue for our youngest daughter, lyra. getting her medical attention was the right decision. we had no idea, however, what a fire-storm it would end up creating on land about the parenting choices of sailors.
.
the hardest part of this whole ordeal was not the massive media attention our story created, but the traumatic rescue itself and the loss of our home and our decade long dream to circumnavigate the world together. we spent the first few weeks of our return to land taking care of lyra, who continued to deal with several rounds of her illness, and trying to make sense of the abbreviation of our dream. it took us many years to overcome the loss and the story still reverberates throughout our lives.
.
almost two years ago i began to write a book about our experience. the book tells the unlikely story of how my husband and i met (a story i've never told publicly) and how we bought a sailboat, raised our kids aboard, and ended up in that dramatic rescue at sea.
.
i'm sharing this today because in the next month or two my book will go out on submission and iâ€™ll need a team of people who can help me get the word out about it. iâ€™ll be looking to do speakings & readings at book stores, libraries, sailing clubs, events, etc. and for ideas on podcasts and websites where i can talk about the themes in my story including: adventure, sailing, free-range parenting, mental health,Â #metooÂ and speaking out against sexual abuse.
.
part of publishing a book is publicity and marketing and for that iâ€™ll need your help. the group is an inclusive place where we can talk about the process of writing and publishing. itâ€™s a safe place too, for us to share our stories and support each other, and ultimately, to help theÂ #rebelheartbookÂ make its way into the world.
.
iâ€™ll need a crew of people to help me through this process. will you join me there? we can connect our rebel hearts together:
.
here's the group:Â facebook.com/groups/charlottekaufmangroup
.
if facebook isnâ€™t your thing, you can get updates by email:Â bit.ly/charlotteemaillist
.
<3 charlotte
.
#rebelheartbook #kidsonboatsÂ #womenwhosail

text:
accountability, change of heart, and even peace are all possible in the light of the truth.
_____________________________
"and do not participate in the unfruitful deeds of darkness, but instead even expose them.... but all things before visible when they are exposed by the light, for everything that becomes visible is light". ephesians 5 ,vv. 11,13
_____________________________
sometimes you want it to just go away. the result is a "can't talk" system in which problems get swept under the carpet and people (leaders) are not held accountable for their actions. 
but i'm learning that's just false peace... which really means there is no peace. it's not possible to maintain something that's not there.
if something is wrong address it. otherwise it will just grow out of control.
#biblejournaling #bibleverse #justiceforvictims #speaktruth #thetruthwillsetyoufree #bebrave #leadershipdevelopment #ministry #mommydiaries #spiritualabuse

text_retweet:
reposted from @muzakkani1996 -  reposted from @backto_muslimidentity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, â€œpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai â€˜amanahâ€™ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa â€˜kontrol seksualâ€™ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.â€ kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. â€œmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,â€ ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, â€œtidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaula

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: â€œwe exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.â€ documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takersâ€™ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebookâ€™s â€œplatform policyâ€ allowed only collection of friendsâ€™ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebookâ€™s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate â€œinformation warfareâ€ against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with ficial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
some things never change.... yes bey logan (aka simon bully), the would be harvey winestain, the man who when accused if sexual misconduct made the disturbingly rapey reply "its more what i tried to do than what i actually did'....and "â€œmany of the accusations made against me are either untrue or taken out of context.', the human cockroach is still crawling around threatening people and hiding behind his kids as he does so

today he decides to threaten a very good friend arne venema , and this at the same time he's claiming to have changed for the better

i had the misfortune to know him for a very long time and he went from cocky to full on sociopath and scumbag, and i have lost count of how many times he has claimed to have been responsible for peoples success (but only says when they aren't in the room!) how he would destroy me or other people and stop us from working... we're all still here!

i still remember his epic rant at filmart a few years back where he stomps up to me, puts on a deep voice "you know what the problem with filmart is? (dramatic pause) too many witnesses' before running away

but i guess its easier to abuse women and take advanatge of their naivity than anything else, you really a low life scumbag and i would have hoped that the #metoo revelations about you would have taught you a lesson.... instead you boast of it.... a normal person would have learnt their lesson and would be trying to make amends while a completely deranged idiot continues down that path..... a full investigation of him and his activities still needs to be done, there's a lot of people who know what he did and in certain cases have covered up for him, and that makes you just as much of a fucking scumbag as he is.. and to those who have been his victims, step forward, we'll stand by you.... don't let this guy continue to get away with this shit on any level

#metoo #byelogan #scumbag #rolex

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

according to cou documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the cou documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
at the #philippinereadersandwritersfestival last year, i got this signed copy of "manila was a long time ago" and metaphorically, it came with a passport.
â–«
the author whisked me away to the places i've never been to (except manila) yet seemed familiar from the settings of some of the stories i've readâ€”quebec, berlin, new york, paris, the vatican, san francisco, athens , milan, amsterdam, Ã¥hus, budapest, singapore, phuket, prague and venice. its stories are atmospheric and richly told through varied forms, genre and treatment. one of the stories is pan de regla whose excerpt i've already read in philippine panorama before the book was published. it's nice to read the story in full. it's a familiar narrative of the #metoo era with its tale of lifelong trauma.
â–«
the inspiring preface of this book also struck me, aplenty of musings and wisdom about writing and life.
â–«
"life doesn't get easier when your dreams come true. the chances of falling off the edge, down to the very bottom, are so many as the chances of reaching the peak in one giant leap are so few, at least for me, for whom nothing is ever served on a silver platter. it will take a million small steps to get further to the top, if that's even possible, but one wrong move, or a single misstep, or a moment's carelessness is all it takes to plunge deep, not just back to step one, but back to zero, even below zero. still, i am comforted to know that my fantasies, as much a part of me as the facts of my life, are not subject to gravity. even from the bottom, after my practice of a lifetime, i know i can always choose to look up. or like i have just done here, i can write fiction."
â–«
â€¦for us to read them.
â–«

text:
beautiful jen is going on a hunting trip with her millionaire boyfriend and his two friends. the perfect vacation turns into a nightmare as jen is severely injured and left for dead. as she fights her way back she has to accept her dark side. this is not your average #metoo story.

the horror movie genre is filled with female protagonists who punish men for their wrongdoings, and revenge is the latest stylish, adrenaline filled entry with an electronic soundtrack and buckets of blood. the kills are violent and effective but what makes revenge work is its slick cinematography: the stillness of the desert is somewhat claustrophobic and the action is intense, with quick cuts that reveal just enough to have you gasping for air. 
the movie does a good job setting up the lavish and seemingly safe atmosphere of the million dollar mansion, and even the villains are charismatic and friendly. until the shit hits the fan. how little is required for the things to go very wrong!

the film would not work without a tour de force performance from young matilda lutz (rings). her transition from glamorous, sexy and slightly unlikable girl who sleeps with married men into a killer on the path of vengeance is not very believable, but is thoroughly entertaining.

revenge is showing in australia as a part of french film festival. #moviereview #horrormovies #horrormoviereviews #frenchmovie #frenchfilmfestival #alliancefrancaise #revengethemovie

beautiful jen is going on a hunting trip with her millionaire boyfriend and his two friends. the perfect vacation turns into a nightmare as jen is severely injured and left for dead. as she fights her way back she has to accept her dark side. this is not your average  story.

the horror movie genre is filled with female protagonists who punish men for their wrongdoings, and revenge is the latest stylish, adrenaline filled entry with an electronic soundtrack and buckets of blood. the kills are violent and effective but what makes revenge work is its slick cinematography: the stillness of the dese is somewhat claustrophobic and the action is intense, with quick cuts that reveal just enough to have you gasping for air. 
the movie does a good job setting up the lavish and seemingly safe atmosphere of the million dollar mansion, and even the villains are charismatic and friendly. until the shit hits the fan. how little is required for the things to go very wrong!

the film would not work without a tour de force performance from young matilda lutz (rings). her transition from glamorous, sexy and slightly unlikable girl who sleeps with married men into a killer on the path of vengeance is not very believable, but is thoroughly enteaining.

text:
poem below
.
.
.
.

thud, the noise made as i felt my head
 thrust hard against a closed car door
in minutes like years "i" was me no more
.
.
.
locked in and blinded by pain in darkness even after pleas of "no, please no" ignored
spoken but unheard still you carried on .
.
.

left battered and bruised, a body used
in ways that passangers didn't condone
exiting, not daring to look, left all alone
.
.
.
the grevious act scarring down to bone
concealed by tinted panes your crimes
that stole the fight from  inside of me
.
.
.

my life went out with those very lights
and in the next morning as the sun rose
in the coming of day revealed harm done
.
.
.
yet more pictures for just another file
the swelling went down and the purples
covering shaking limbs faded with time
.
.
.
but the blackness was not  bleached out
as baths taken, attempts to clean memory
raw as skin scrubbed to remove blame
.
.
.
as a victim of circumstance mercilessly
trying to cleanse the flashbacks that took
my breath with the parts of self demised
.
.
.
 the moon rose eternally and set like fear
that crept over me, oh i wished it had all
been over so many times after that night
.
.
.
eventually i arose in medicated reality
a grave within me of all that used to be
filled with a strong will to surely survive
.
.
.
